          </div>
          <div class="trust-stack">
            <article><span>01</span><div><h3>Main drain cleaning</h3><p>The main drain or sewer line connects your property to the municipal sewer system or your septic tank, and blockages here can lead to major disruptions. We specialize in main drain cleaning to remove debris like grease, waste, and roots, prevent backups caused by severe clogs, and safeguard connections throughout your property.</p></div></article>
            <article><span>02</span><div><h3>Kitchen drain cleaning</h3><p>Kitchen sinks frequently become clogged with grease, food particles, or soap residue. Our services help clear blockages quickly to prevent leaks and unpleasant odors, and restore proper flow without damaging your pipes.</p></div></article>
            <article><span>03</span><div><h3>Bathroom drain cleaning</h3><p>Hair, soap scum, and hygiene products can wreak havoc on shower drains, sinks, and tubs. Our process efficiently clears the buildup to address slow-draining fixtures and blockages, and prevents issues like water damage and mold growth.</p></div></article>
            <article><span>04</span><div><h3>Toilet drain cleaning</h3><p>A clogged toilet can lead to unsanitary backups or overflows. We help remove excessive toilet paper, hygiene items, or other obstructions to avoid damaging your drain system and restore normal function quickly.</p></div></article>
            <article><span>05</span><div><h3>Laundry drains and floor drains</h3><p>Lint, detergent residue, and dirt are common causes of laundry room or floor drain clogs, especially in basements and garages. Our team supports clear drains by preventing standing water and potential structural damage.</p></div></article>
            <article><span>06</span><div><h3>Outdoor drain cleaning</h3><p>Leaves, dirt, and debris can clog outdoor drains, causing water to pool around your yard, driveway, or foundation. We clean and clear yard drains, landscape drains, French drains, and storm drains to keep water flowing properly, especially before or after heavy rainfall.</p></div></article>
