            <p class="eyebrow">Cleaning frequency</p>
            <h2>How often should drains be cleaned?</h2>
            <p>The frequency of drain cleaning depends on factors like usage, pipe condition, and the type of drain. We recommend these general guidelines:</p>
            <ul class="check-list">
              <li>High-use drains (kitchens and bathrooms) should be cleaned every 6 to 12 months.</li>
              <li>Outdoor drains and main sewer lines should, at least, be cleaned once annually, or more often if surrounded by trees or heavy debris.</li>
              <li>Preventative maintenance plans are available for regularly scheduled cleanings based on your specific needs, to help catch issues early.</li>
            </ul>
            <p>Establishing a regular cleaning routine with a professional drain cleaning company like Honest Drain can extend the life of your drain and sewer system and reduce emergency repairs.</p>
          </div>
          <div>
            <p class="eyebrow">Avoid DIY pitfalls</p>
            <h2>The pitfalls of DIY drain cleaning</h2>
            <p>While store-bought chemicals and home remedies may temporarily fix clogs, they often fail to address the underlying issues. Attempting DIY solutions can lead to:</p>
            <ul class="check-list">
              <li><strong>Pipe damage:</strong> Harsh chemicals may corrode or weaken pipes over time.</li>
              <li><strong>Missed blockages:</strong> Without professional tools, clogs deeper in your system go unnoticed.</li>
              <li><strong>Inefficient repairs:</strong> Temporary fixes do not address the root cause, leading to recurring problems.</li>
            </ul>
            <p>Professional drain cleaning services ensure effective and thorough care, preserving the integrity of your drain system.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
